#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:51
msgid "### `groupadd` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:56
msgid ""
"The `groupadd` command adds a group to the system.  ``` groupadd [-f] [-g "
"GID] group ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:62
msgid "``` $ sudo groupadd -g 1012 GroupeB ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:68
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Option  |\tDescription                   |\n"
"| --------| ----------------------------- |\n"
"|`-g GID` |\t`GID` of the group to create. |\n"
"|`-f` |\tThe system chooses a `GID` if the one specified by the `-g` option already exists. |\n"
"|`-r` |\tCreates a system group with a `GID` between `SYS_GID_MIN` and `SYS_GID_MAX`. These two variables are defined in `/etc/login.defs`. |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:70
msgid "Group naming rules:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:73
msgid "No accents or special characters;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:73
msgid "Different from the name of an existing user or system files."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:76
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Note\n"
"    Under **Debian**, the administrator should use, except in scripts intended to be portable to all Linux distributions, the `addgroup` and `delgroup` commands as specified in the `man`:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:85
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    ```\n"
"    $ man addgroup\n"
"    DESCRIPTION\n"
"    adduser and addgroup add users and groups to the system according to command line options and configuration information\n"
"    in /etc/adduser.conf. They are friendlier front ends to the low level tools like useradd, groupadd and usermod programs,\n"
"    by default choosing Debian policy conformant UID and GID values, creating a home directory with skeletal configuration,\n"
"    running a custom script, and other features.\n"
"    ```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:87
msgid "### Command `groupmod`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:89
msgid ""
"The `groupmod` command allows you to modify an existing group on the system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:93
msgid "``` groupmod [-g GID] [-n nom] group ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:100
msgid "``` $ sudo groupmod -g 1016 GroupP $ sudo groupmod -n GroupC GroupB ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:105
msgid ""
"|Option |\tDescription | | ------| ----------- | |`-g GID` |\tNew `GID` of "
"the group to modify.  |`-n name` | New name."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:107
msgid ""
"It is possible to change the name of a group, its `GID` or both "
"simultaneously."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:109
msgid ""
"After modification, the files belonging to the group have an unknown `GID`. "
"They must be reassigned the new `GID`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:113
msgid "``` $ sudo find / -gid 1002 -exec chgrp 1016 {} \\; ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:115
msgid "### `groupdel` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:117
msgid ""
"The `groupdel` command is used to delete an existing group on the system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:121
msgid "``` groupdel group ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:127
msgid "``` $ sudo groupdel GroupC ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:130
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Tip\n"
"    To be deleted, a group must no longer contain users.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:132
msgid ""
"Deleting the last user of an eponymous group will cause the system to delete "
"the group."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:135
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Tip\n"
"    Each group has a unique `GID`. A group can be duplicated. By convention, the `GID` of system groups range from 0 (`root`) to 999.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:138
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Tip\n"
"    Since a user is necessarily part of a group, it is best to create the groups before adding the users. Therefore, a group may not have any members.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:140
msgid "### `/etc/group` file"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:142
msgid "This file contains the group information (separated by `:`)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:148
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```\n"
"$ sudo tail -1 /etc/group\n"
"GroupP:x:516:patrick\n"
"  (1)  (2)(3)   (4)\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:153
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:171
msgid "1: Name of the group."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:153
msgid "2: Password (`x` if defined in `/etc/gshadow`)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:153
msgid "3: GID."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:153
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:171
msgid "4: Guest members (separated by commas, does not contain core members)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:156
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Note\n"
"    Each line in the `/etc/group` file corresponds to a group. Users whose group is their main group are not listed at this level. This membership information is in fact already provided by the `/etc/passwd` file...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:158
msgid "### `/etc/gshadow` file"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:160
msgid ""
"This file contains the security information about the groups (separated by `:"
"`)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:166
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```\n"
"$ sudo grep GroupA /etc/gshadow\n"
"GroupA:$6$2,9,v...SBn160:alain:rockstar\n"
"   (1)      (2)            (3)      (4)\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:171
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:417
msgid "2: Encrypted password."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:171
msgid "3: Administrator of the group."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:174
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Warning\n"
"    For each line in the `/etc/group` file there must be a corresponding line in the `/etc/gshadow` file.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:177
msgid ""
"A `!` in the password indicates that it is locked.  Thus no user can use the "
"password to access the group (since group members do not need it)."
msgstr ""

