#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:204
msgid "### `useradd` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:206
msgid "The `useradd` command is used to add a user."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:210
msgid "``` useradd [-u UID] [-g GID] [-d directory] [-s shell] login ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:216
msgid "``` $ sudo useradd -u 1000 -g 1013 -d /home/GroupC/carine carine ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:226
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Option        |\tDescription                                                        |\n"
"| --------------| ------------------------------------------------------------------ |\n"
"|`-u UID`       |\t`UID` of the user to create.                                       |\n"
"|`-g GID`       |\t`GID` of the main group.                                           |\n"
"|`-d directory` |\tHome directory.                                                    |\n"
"|`-s shell`     | Shell.                                                             |\n"
"|`-c`           | Add a comment.                                                     |\n"
"|`-U`           | Adds the user to a group with the same name created simultaneously.|\n"
"|`-M`           | Does not create the connection directory.                          |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:228
msgid "At creation, the account has no password and is locked."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:230
msgid "A password must be assigned to unlock the account."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:232
msgid "Account naming rules:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:236
msgid "No accents, capital letters or special characters;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:236
msgid "Different from the name of an existing group or system file;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:236
msgid "Set the options `-u`, `-g`, `-d` and `-s` at creation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:239
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Warning\n"
"    The home directory tree must be created except for the last directory.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:241
msgid ""
"The last directory is created by the `useradd` command, which takes the "
"opportunity to copy the files from `/etc/skel` into it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:243
#, no-wrap
msgid "**A user can belong to several groups in addition to their main group.**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:245
msgid "For secondary groups, the `-G` option must be used."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:251
msgid "``` $ sudo useradd -u 1000 -g GroupA -G GroupP,GroupC albert ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:254
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Note\n"
"    Under **Debian**, you will have to specify the `-m` option to force the creation of the login directory or set the `CREATE_HOME` variable in the `/etc/login.defs` file. In all cases, the administrator should use the `adduser` and `deluser` commands as specified in the `man`, except in scripts intended to be portable to all Linux distributions:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:261
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    ```\n"
"    $ man useradd\n"
"    DESCRIPTION\n"
"        **useradd** is a low level utility for adding users. On Debian, administrators should usually use **adduser(8)**\n"
"         instead.\n"
"    ```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:263
msgid "#### Default value for user creation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:265
msgid "Modification of the file `/etc/default/useradd`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:269
msgid "``` useradd -D [-b directory] [-g group] [-s shell] ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:275
msgid "``` $ sudo useradd -D -g 1000 -b /home -s /bin/bash ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:284
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Option         | \tDescription                                                                 |\n"
"| -------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n"
"| `-D`           | Sets the default values for user creation.                                   |\n"
"| `-b directory` | Sets the default login directory.                                            |\n"
"| `-g group`     | Sets the default group.                                                      |\n"
"| `-s shell`     | Sets the default shell.                                                      |\n"
"| `-f`           | The number of days after the password expires before the account is disabled.|\n"
"| `-e`           | The date the account will be disabled.                                       |\n"
msgstr ""

