#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:429
msgid "### Modification commands"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:431
msgid "#### `chown` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:436
msgid ""
"The `chown` command allows you to change the owners of a file.  ``` chown [-"
"R] [-v] login[:group] file ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:442
msgid ""
"Examples: ``` $ sudo chown root myfile $ sudo chown albert:GroupA myfile ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:447
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Option |\tDescription                                           |\n"
"| ------ | ------------------------------------------------------ |\n"
"| `-R`   |\tChanges the owners of the directory and its contents. |\n"
"| `-v`   |\tDisplays the executed changes.                        |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:449
msgid "To change only the owner user:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:453
msgid "``` $ sudo chown albert file ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:455
msgid "To modify only the owner group:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:459
msgid "``` $ sudo chown :GroupA file ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:461
msgid "Changing the user and owner group:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:465
msgid "``` $ sudo chown albert:GroupA file ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:467
msgid ""
"In the following example the group assigned will be the main group of the "
"specified user."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:471
msgid "``` $ sudo chown albert: file ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:473
msgid "### `chgrp` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:475
msgid "The `chgrp` command allows you to change the owner group of a file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:479
msgid "``` chgrp [-R] [-v] group file ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:484
msgid "Example: ``` $ sudo chgrp group1 file ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:489
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Option | Description                                                              |\n"
"| ------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------ |\n"
"| `-R`   | Modifies the owner groups of the directory and its contents (recursion). |\n"
"| `-v`   | Displays the executed changes.                                           |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:492
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Note\n"
"    It is possible to apply to a file an owner and an owner group by taking as reference those of another file:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:496
msgid "``` chown [options] --reference=RRFILE FILE ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:502
msgid "``` chown --reference=/etc/groups /etc/passwd ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:504
msgid "## Guest management"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:506
msgid "### `gpasswd` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:508
msgid "The command `gpasswd` allows to manage a group."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:512
msgid "``` gpasswd [-a login] [-A login] [-d login] [-M login] group ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:519
msgid ""
"``` $ sudo gpasswd -A alain GroupA [alain]$ gpasswd -a patrick GroupA ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:526
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Option     |\tDescription                         |\n"
"| ---------- | ------------------------------------ |\n"
"| `-a login` |\tAdds the user to the group.         |\n"
"| `-A login` |\tSets the group administrator.       |\n"
"| `-d login` |\tRemove the user from the group.     |\n"
"| `-M login` |\tDefines the complete list of guests.|\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:533
msgid ""
"The command `gpasswd -M` acts as a modification, not an addition.  ``` # "
"gpasswd GroupeA New Password : Re-enter new password : ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:535
msgid "### `id` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:545
msgid ""
"The `id` command displays the group names of a user.  ``` id login ``` "
"Example: ``` $ sudo id alain uid=1000(alain) gid=1000(GroupA) "
"groupes=1000(GroupA),1016(GroupP)  ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:547
msgid "### `newgrp` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:556
msgid ""
"The `newgrp` command allows you to temporarily use a secondary group for "
"file creation.  ``` newgrp [secondarygroups] ``` Example: ``` [alain]$ "
"newgrp GroupB ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:559
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Note\n"
"    After using this command, the files will be created with the `GID` of its subgroup.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:561
msgid "The command `newgrp` without parameters reassigns the main group."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:563
msgid "## Securing"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:565
msgid "### `passwd` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:575
msgid ""
"The `passwd` command is used to manage a password.  ``` passwd [-d] [-l] [-"
"S] [-u] [login] ``` Examples: ``` $ sudo passwd -l albert $ sudo passwd -n "
"60 -x 90 -w 80 -i 10 patrick ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:587
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Option | Description                                            |\n"
"| ------ | ------------------------------------------------------ |\n"
"| `-d` | Removes the password.                                    |\n"
"| `-l` | Locks the account.                                       |\n"
"| `-S` | Displays the account status.                             |\n"
"| `-u` | Unlocks the account.                                     |\n"
"| `-e` | Expires the password.                                    |\n"
"| `-n days` | Minimum password lifetime.                          |\n"
"| `-x days` | Maximum password lifetime.                          |\n"
"| `-w days` | Warning time before expiration.                     |\n"
"| `-i days` | Delay before deactivation when the password expires.|\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:589
msgid ""
"With the `passwd` command, locking an account is accomplished by adding `!!` "
"before the password in the `/etc/shadow` file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:591
msgid ""
"Using the command `usermod -U` command only removes one of the `!`. So the "
"account remains locked."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:595
msgid "Alain changes his password:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:599
msgid "``` [alain]$ passwd ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:601
msgid "root changes Alain's password"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:605
msgid "``` $ sudo passwd alain ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:608
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Note\n"
"    The `passwd` command is available to users to change their password (the old password is requested). The administrator can change the passwords of all users without restriction.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:610
msgid "They will have to comply with the security restrictions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:612
msgid ""
"When managing user accounts by shell script, it may be useful to set a "
"default password after creating the user."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:614
msgid "This can be done by passing the password to the `passwd` command."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:621
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Example:\n"
"```\n"
"$ sudo echo \"azerty,1\" | passwd --stdin philippe\n"
"```\n"
"!!! Warning\n"
"    The password is entered in clear text, `passwd` takes care of encrypting it.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:623
msgid "### `chage` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:632
msgid ""
"The `chage` command is used to manage the account strategy.  ``` chage [-d "
"date] [-E date] [-I days] [-l] [-m days] [-M days] [-W days] [login] ``` "
"Example: ``` $ sudo chage -m 60 -M 90 -W 80 -I 10 alain ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:642
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Option | Description                                    |\n"
"| ------ | ---------------------------------------------- |\n"
"| `-I days` | Delay before deactivation, password expired.|\n"
"| `-l`      | Displays the policy details.                |\n"
"| `-m days` | Minimum lifetime of the password.           |\n"
"| `-M days` | Maximum lifetime of the password.           |\n"
"| `-d AAAA-MM-JJ` | Last password change.                 |\n"
"| `-E AAAA-MM-JJ` | Account expiration date.              |\n"
"| `-W days` | Warning time before expiration.             |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:644
msgid "The `chage` command also offers an interactive mode."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:646
msgid "The `-d` option forces the password to be changed at login."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:652
msgid "Examples: ``` $ sudo chage philippe $ sudo chage -d 0 philippe ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:655
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Note\n"
"    If no user is specified, the order will concern the user who enters it.\n"
msgstr ""

