msgid "## Identity change"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:725
msgid "### `su` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:727
msgid ""
"The `su` command allows you to change the identity of the connected user."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:731
msgid "``` su [-] [-c command] [login] ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:738
msgid "``` $ sudo su - alain [albert]$ su -c \"passwd alain\" ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:743
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Option | Description                                           |\n"
"| ------ | ----------------------------------------------------- |\n"
"| `-` |\tLoads the user's complete environment.                   |\n"
"| `-c` command |\tExecutes the command under the user's identity.|\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:745
msgid "If the login is not specified, it will be `root`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:747
msgid "Standard users will have to type the password for the new identity."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:750
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Tip\n"
"    There are successive 'layers' created (a stack of `bash` environments). To switch from one user to another, you must first type the `exit` command to take back your identity and then the `su` command to take another identity.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:752
msgid "#### Profile loading"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:754
msgid "`root` endorses the identity of the user `alain` with `su`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:761
msgid "``` ...  /home/GroupA/alain/.bashrc /etc/bashrc ...  ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:763
msgid "`root` assumes the identity of the user `alain` with `su -`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:771
msgid ""
"``` ...  /home/GroupA/alain/.bash_profile /home/GroupA/alain/.bashrc /etc/"
"bashrc ...  ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:773
msgid ""
"A user can temporarily (for another command or an entire session) assume the "
"identity of another account."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:775
msgid "If no user is specified, the command will be for `root` (`su -`)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:777
msgid ""
"It is necessary to know the password of the user whose identity is being "
"endorsed unless it is `root` that is executing the command."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/06-users.md:778
msgid ""
"An administrator can thus work on a standard user account and use the rights "
"of the `root` account only occasionally."
msgstr ""
